description:
## Problem
All 40+ theme CSS files are imported synchronously at app startup via `apps/ui/src/styles/theme-imports.ts`, which is imported by `app.tsx` (line 11). This loads ~140-200KB of CSS regardless of which single theme the user has active. Users only ever use one theme at a time.

## Current Behavior
`theme-imports.ts` contains 40+ synchronous imports:
```typescript
import './themes/dark.css';
import './themes/retro.css';
import './themes/dracula.css';
import './themes/nord.css';
// ... 36 more themes
```

The `apps/ui/src/styles/themes/` directory contains 41 CSS files, each 2-7KB.

## Required Changes
1. Create a dynamic theme loader utility (`apps/ui/src/lib/theme-loader.ts`) that imports theme CSS on demand using Vite's dynamic `import()`
2. Keep the current/default theme (dark) loaded synchronously to prevent flash of unstyled content
3. Load the user's saved theme on startup (from `getStoredTheme()` in `app-store.ts`)
4. When user switches themes, dynamically load the new theme CSS
5. Consider preloading the next/previous themes in the theme picker for instant switching during preview
6. Remove bulk imports from `theme-imports.ts`
7. Ensure the existing `applyStoredTheme()` function in `__root.tsx` (lines 57-77) still works - it applies theme classes before React hydration to prevent flash

## Pattern to Follow
```typescript
// apps/ui/src/lib/theme-loader.ts
const themeCache = new Set<string>();

export async function loadTheme(themeName: string): Promise<void> {
  if (themeCache.has(themeName)) return; // Already loaded
  if (themeName === 'light' || themeName === 'dark') {
    // Base themes loaded synchronously
    themeCache.add(themeName);
    return;
  }
  await import(`../styles/themes/${themeName}.css`);
  themeCache.add(themeName);
}
```

## Files to Modify
- Create: `apps/ui/src/lib/theme-loader.ts` - Dynamic theme loading utility
- `apps/ui/src/styles/theme-imports.ts` - Remove all imports, keep only dark.css as default
- `apps/ui/src/routes/__root.tsx` - Call loadTheme() when deferredTheme changes (around line 747-765)
- `apps/ui/src/components/views/settings-view/appearance/appearance-section.tsx` - Preload themes on picker hover
- May need to update `apps/ui/src/app.tsx` to load stored theme on mount

## Expected Impact
- Initial CSS payload reduced by ~130-190KB (only 1 theme loaded instead of 40)
- Faster initial paint and CSS parsing
- Theme switching remains instant for cached themes

## Acceptance Criteria
- Only the active theme CSS is loaded on initial page load (verify in Network tab)
- Theme switching works correctly with no flash of unstyled content
- Hovering over themes in the appearance settings preloads them for instant preview
- Previously loaded themes are cached and don't re-fetch
- The `applyStoredTheme()` pre-hydration function still prevents theme flash on page load
